text: Joseph Cottet (14 April 1923 – 23 May 2019) was a Swiss politician. He was born in Bossonnens. He served as a member of the Grand Council of Fribourg for the Party of Farmers, Traders and Independents from 1957 to 1971. Cottet later served in the National Council as a member of the People's Party from 1983 to 1987. Cottet died on 23 May 2019, at the age of 96. ==References== ==Other websites== * Joseph Cottet – National Council profile Category:1923 births Category:2019 deaths Category:People from the canton of Fribourg Category:Swiss politicians
